<h1 class="heading-large">Submit a proposal for flood and coastal erosion risk management (FCERM) project funding</h1>

<h2 class="heading-medium">Use this service to:</h2>
<ul class="list-bullet">
  <li>start, review or update a proposal for flood and coastal erosion risk management (FCERM) project funding</li>
  <li>submit or resubmit a proposal</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="heading-medium">Before you start</h3>
<p>
You will need a FCERM project funding account in order to use this service.
</p>
<p>
If you have an account, you can start and save a project proposal but to complete and submit a project proposal you will need:
</p>
<p>
  <ul class="list-bullet">
    <li>to know the outcomes you expect to achieve, including the number of households benefiting</li>
    <li>to know the amount of funding required, including expected contributions, and when this is going to be spent</li>
    <li>an estimate of the whole life costs and benefits discounted to today's values. The <%= link_to t(".partnership_funding_guidance_link"), t(".partnership_funding_guidance_link_target"), target: "_blank" %> and <%= link_to t(".multi_coloured_manual_link"), t(".multi_coloured_manual_link_target"), rel: "external", target: "_blank" %> can help you.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3 class="heading-medium">If you don't have an account</h3>
<p>
You can <%= link_to t('request_an_account_link'), pafs_core.new_account_request_path %> if you work for:
</p>
<p>
  <ul class="list-bullet">
    <li>a risk management authority</li>
    <li>partnership and strategic overview team</li>
    <li>an area programming team</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<div class="form-group">
  <p>
    <%= link_to t('.start_now'), pafs_core.projects_path, class: "button button-start", role: "button" %>
  </p>
</div>
